<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Although the variable $_SERVER['HTTPS'] should be empty when it isn't a HTTPS request, a few webserver set the value to 'off'. The PHP reference manual ([<a href="http://at.php.net/manual/en/reserved.variables.server.php">http://at.php.net/manual/en/â€¦</a>]) mentions IIS and I encountered the problem with Abyss webserver. If the value is set to 'off', Action_Helper_Redirector redirects the request to https which is wrong.
Therefore the Action_Helper_Redirector should be changed in function  *_redirect($url)* from</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$proto = (empty($_SERVER['HTTPS'])) ? 'http' : 'https';
</code></pre>

<p>to</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$proto = ((empty($_SERVER['HTTPS'])) || (strcasecmp($_SERVER['HTTPS'],'off') == 0)) ? 'http' : 'https';
</code></pre>

